  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the Coordination of Humanitarian Assistance through the Monitoring of Population Movements of People with Acute Shocks</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM is contributing to improving the emergency lifesaving humanitarian response in Central African Republic (CAR) by collect and analyze data that can inform the humanitarian community on the latest population movements and the humanitarian impacts linked to one-off crises more precisely and more rapidly. Moreover, through its monitoring of population movements, IOM will contribute to feed into the development-humanitarian nexus by adequately informing the situation of return to CAR and the multi-sectoral needs of the area for the implementation of durable solutions.</narrative>
  </description>
